english:
  title: Sending Off a Traveler
  author: Jung Jisung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The rain has cleared on the long embankment where the grass shines green.
    I send you toward the southern shore, my voice breaking into a sorrowful song.
    When will the waters of the Daedong River ever run dry?
    Year after year, my tears of parting swell the waves.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Daedong River (大同江) flows through Pyongyang in present-day North Korea, historically an important site of farewell and separation in Korean poetry.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'southern shore' (南浦) refers to a riverside area traditionally associated with partings and journeys in East Asian poetic tradition.
